column1: |I appeared on ⁦@komonews⁩ this week to discuss the 737MAX #COVID19 relief and the next Congress. ⁦@WaDems38thLD⁩  ⁦@32Dems ⁦@1stLDDems⁩ ⁦@skagitdemocrats ⁩ Connect to Congress: Rep. Rick Larsen || KOMO https://t.co/eGulSOEsFf|
Join #TeamLarsen for socially distant sign waving throughout the 2nd District to help Get Out the Vote ahead of #ElectionDay. Find a sign waving event in your neighborhood ➡️ https://t.co/TIqWcngvzy.
Great news! I will continue to fight for critical COVID-19 relief. https://t.co/hwQWazqTou

Protecting our local small businesses is an easy way to ensure that our friends and neighbors are able to stay safe and healthy during the COVID-19 Crisis.  Senate Republicans must pass the HEROES Act NOW to expand the vital aid given to our local workers and businesses

ICYMI: "More than 250 Whatcom County businesses received grants under the Whatcom ReStart program funded by last spring’s federal coronavirus relief package officials announced this week."  https://t.co/aAqMJnd3qP
@WhoseRyanStiles Hatch Act Hack Act Boring Orange Coronavirus Crunch Rocky Road to November Vanilla Only Vanilla Always Vanilla

Also visited local small businesses that received PPP loans to discuss how the loan helped save jobs and why we need to include more gmhelp in COVID 19 relief bill; and started distributing a white paper on actions I have taken to save #USPSisEssential https://t.co/DqBGdWnwOe

I visited 20+ small businesses this week across #WA02 that benefited from federal Paycheck Protection Program loans during the COVID-19 pandemic. Check out @WhidbeyNews' story on my stop in #OakHarbor ⬇️ https://t.co/dmctA7TuLI
Together we can expand health care access fight climate change & protect voting rights. I will continue to fight for working families who have been affected by COVID-19. 4/4

Wrapping up our first day of socially distant sign waving with a stop in Mountlake Terrace.   Grab a mask and join us tomorrow! Our first stop is in Everett (Rucker & 41st) at 8:30 a.m. #GOTV https://t.co/00SbdlX7Z7
Kicking off our three day GOTV sign waving tour with a socially distant stop in Lynnwood!   Visit https://t.co/TIqWcngvzy to find a sign waving location near you. https://t.co/A2LtFUMDNs
I went live on Facebook to give an update on Congress and the next COVID-19 relief package. Check it out ⬇️ https://t.co/yyMmRso4ly

Expanding access to high-quality affordable health care is essential especially as we continue to face COVID-19.   Today I voted for the Patient Protection & Affordable Care Enhancement Act to build on the #ACA by lowering health costs and prescription drug prices.

Thank you @nwcarpenters members for your help with socially distant sign building.  Want a yard sign? Email jack@ricklarsen.org or visit https://t.co/RTv7ZffgsG and we will get one to you. With just three weeks until ballots drop now is the time to get involved! https://t.co/GVYtW0YPJw

#AllInWA is putting on a virtual concert tomorrow to raise funds for #WA workers and families who have been impacted by COVID-19. Head to their Facebook event page for more information on how to tune in: https://t.co/veO773vkka.
Tomorrow at 5:30 p.m. I am hosting a virtual fireside chat with European travel guru @RickSteves to talk about COVID-19 and travel and to answer your questions.   Join us ➡️ https://t.co/lllEmdp7sh.

I went live on Facebook yesterday with @SuzanDelBene to talk about racial justice COVID-19 response vote-by-mail the Supreme Court LGBTQ+ ruling and much more including her time as a football referee. Tune in here: https://t.co/fKorE1KC6e.

The @WANationalGuard has hit a major milestone: Troops have packaged more than 25 million pounds of food for local food banks during the COVID-19 pandemic.   No one should go hungry. We must continue to fund and expand programs that help feed Northwest Washington families.

Today the House Transportation Committee held a hearing on the impacts of COVID-19 on transportation workers. Tune in ➡️ https://t.co/JrE3ugowoz. Thank you front line transportation workers for your sacrifices and hard work.
I am going live on Facebook tomorrow at 4:30 p.m. to give an update on COVID-19 and Congress before I head to D.C. to vote on the Democrats' next relief package.   Tune in: https://t.co/sxUTAVxeJR

Uninsured individuals affected by COVID-19 have until 5:30 p.m. tonight to sign up for health coverage during the special enrollment period through @WAplanfinder.  More information: https://t.co/k92YGwfa6F
I spoke to @komonews about COVID-19 and responding to the pandemic. Tune in ⬇️ https://t.co/ACRgfH3Yyt
This #NationalNursesDay I want to recognize all of the nurses who are on the front lines of COVID-19. Thank you for your tireless work to keep our communities safe.

🚨 Deadline Alert 🚨 If you do not have health insurance you have until May 8 to sign up for coverage through Washington Healthplanfinder during the COVID-19 special enrollment period.  Visit https://t.co/IZm1s2G3x0 for more information.
Social distancing is working but we are not yet on the other side of COVID-19. Please continue to stay home to help keep our communities safe and healthy. https://t.co/4WZieIEgMr

Thank you to everyone who has been staying home to help slow the spread of COVID-19. I know it is not easy but let's keep it up. We are in this together and we will get through this. https://t.co/89ADkHv86I
If you are looking for a way to help out the @RedCross is seeking people who have recovered from COVID-19 to donate plasma to help current patients.    Learn more: https://t.co/eTl8CYyxjo
This Monday I am going live on Facebook at 11:30 a.m. to give an update on COVID-19 and the interim funding package. Tune in: https://t.co/sxUTAVxeJR

I flew to D.C. to vote for a $484 billion interim COVID-19 relief package that provides aid for small businesses and hospitals and expands testing.  I will keep working to make sure our communities get the help they need. https://t.co/NHD9X7oyA4
Thank you health care workers and first responders. Your work fighting COVID-19 on the front lines is inspiring and I appreciate your sacrifice. https://t.co/7mR1EnAMyX
I held a Facebook Live event today giving updates on COVID-19. Catch it here: https://t.co/mZmxOi0orh
This Friday I will be live on Facebook at 11:30 a.m. to give an update on COVID-19. Join in at https://t.co/sxUTAVxeJR

Be on the lookout for COVID-19 scammers. Watch out for:  ❌Fake cures and vaccines ❌Emails posing as government agencies ❌Sites and apps using COVID-19 info to get access to your devices ❌Donation requests from groups you do not know

Check out my op-ed in @MLTnews about addressing the economic impacts of COVID-19 ➡️ https://t.co/fYsWklDfz7. The public health emergency is real as is the economic emergency and we must tackle both at the same time.
Thanks to everyone who joined my Facebook Live event this afternoon on COVID-19. If you missed it you can tune in here: https://t.co/kpWyb3qUcT
I will be going live on Facebook tomorrow at 4:30 p.m. to give an update on COVID-19. Tune in at https://t.co/sxUTAVxeJR

Over the past few weeks on the political side my campaign team and I have hosted a dozen calls on COVID-19 including with teachers environmental groups organized labor and Indivisible Young Democrats and League of Women Voters members. Thanks to those who called in!
Thank you to all of the health care workers and first responders who are working around the clock on the frontlines to fight COVID-19. https://t.co/awjVbp2uch

House Speaker Nancy Pelosi is creating a bipartisan oversight panel to make sure COVID-19 relief funds are spent effectively a great step to help ensure this critical aid goes to the workers families and small businesses that need it. https://t.co/1HBfKtfxAn

I held calls with folks in Snohomish and Whatcom County last night on the COVID-19 relief package. Reach out to jack@ricklarsen.org if you'd like to dial in to tonight's Skagit County call at 5:30 p.m. https://t.co/gqMIG7ufuY

I’m currently in D.C. to ensure the passage of a COVID-19 relief package to provide much-needed help for workers families and small businesses. Tune in Monday at 11 a.m. for a Facebook Live event on the bill.

I hosted calls tonight with Democratic party members activists and leaders in the San Juan and Island counties on COVID-19 and Congress part of my goal to hold similar conference calls with every county in the district this week.   Thanks to those who called in!
Tomorrow at 11:30 a.m. I'll be conducting my second Facebook Live event on COVID-19 and I hope you'll tune in. Reply with any questions you'd like me to answer.

Today I held two more conference calls on COVID-19. A big thanks to the @IndivisibleTeam and @youngdems members for their questions.   It's my top priority to get information out to the community. https://t.co/mLTbFYuxb4
For COVID-19 information visit the @WADeptHealth site at ➡️ https://t.co/UwZONaPFuj. And for more on prevention visit the @CDCgov site at ➡️ https://t.co/c2uHMAiYMZ. https://t.co/0rYfSTBnXa

I'm working virtually in accordance with local health district recommendations to support the community. This morning I spoke with community leaders and officials over the phone about COVID-19. https://t.co/nEaUGxaktf

I'm working hard to help PNW families whose lives have been upended by the coronavirus.   For more on what I'm doing check out my video: https://t.co/PO9KHZYg61  And for info about COVID-19 visit the @WADeptHealth website: https://t.co/UwZONaPFuj
